        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#oliverio1927"/>, p. <citedRange>157</citedRange></bibl> (mention of find); 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#oliverioTacc"/>, <citedRange>XI.57</citedRange></bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SECir"/>, <citedRange>38</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>095610</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                    <ab>
                     <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-65124"><name nymRef="#Νίκανδρος">Νίκανδρος</name> <persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-63261"><name type="patronymic" nymRef="#Ἀρτυμίων">Ἀρτυμ<lb n="2" break="no"/>ίωνος</name></persName></persName> <w lemma="δεκάτα">δεκάταν</w>
                    </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p>Nikandros fils d'Artymiôn <supplied reason="subaudible">a consacré ce monument</supplied> comme dîme.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p>Nikandros son of Artymion <supplied reason="subaudible">dedicated this monument</supplied> as a tithe.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p>Nikandros figlio di Artymion <supplied reason="subaudible">ha dedicato questo monumento</supplied> come decima.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>The second inscription on the same block was probably aimed at being more clearly seen.</p>
                <p/>
                <p/>
            </div></body>
